## Memory Management in Swift

Swift uses Automatic Reference Counting (ARC) to manage memory.

### How ARC Works

```swift
class Person {
    let name: String
    init(name: String) { self.name = name }
    deinit { print("\(name) is being deallocated") }
}

var person: Person? = Person(name: "John") // ref count = 1
var person2 = person // ref count = 2
person = nil // ref count = 1
person2 = nil // ref count = 0, deinit called
```

### Retain Cycles

```swift
class Person {
    var name: String
    var apartment: Apartment? // Strong reference by default
    init(name: String) { self.name = name }
}

class Apartment {
    var number: Int
    var tenant: Person? // Strong reference - creates retain cycle!
    init(number: Int) { self.number = number }
}
```

### Breaking Retain Cycles with `weak`

```swift
class Person {
    var name: String
    weak var apartment: Apartment? // weak breaks the cycle
    init(name: String) { self.name = name }
}
```

### When to Use `weak`

- Delegate relationships
- Parent-child references where parent can disappear
- Closure capture lists for escaping closures

